The article is a letter from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Speaker of the House regarding an Executive Order he has issued. The Executive Order is in response to the national emergency declared in Executive Order 14024 of April 15, 2021, concerning harmful foreign activities of the Russian Federation. The order prohibits the importation of certain products from Russia, the exportation of luxury goods and other items to Russia, new investments in the Russian economy, the exportation of U.S. dollar-denominated banknotes to Russia, and any approval or financing of transactions that would be prohibited by U.S. persons or within the United States. The President has enclosed a copy of the Executive Order with the letter.